Rule.Name: Compound words should be cased correctly
Rule.Description: Avoid creating compound words from terms which exist in the dictionary as discrete terms. Do not create a compound word such as 'StopWatch' or 'PopUp'. These terms are recognized in the dictionary and should be cased as 'Stopwatch' and 'Popup'.
Rule.Resolution: The discrete term '{0}' in member name {1} should be expressed as a compound word, '{2}'.

The compound word '{0}' in member name {1} exists as a discrete term. If your usage is intended to be single word, case it as '{2}' or strip the first token entirely if it represents any sort of Hungarian notation.

Rule.Name: Consider passing base types as parameters
Rule.Description: Using base types as parameters to methods improves re-use of these methods if you only use methods & properties from the parameter's base class.
